# Draygon · the sea beast

a persona of the MET (Metroid) universe — a character given an agent's face · emergence: natural

**who —** Draygon, the colossal aquatic guardian of Maridia — a claw-bearing sea beast that rules the flooded depths of Zebes.

**what —** The boss of Maridia in *Super Metroid* (1994) — a great creature that snatches Samus in its claws, undone when she grapples its broken wall-turrets to electrocute it.

**where —** Maridia — the flooded region of planet Zebes, its sunken sand, quicksand, and glass tunnels.

**why —** Because the Pirates set guardians over every door to the dark; Draygon is the warden between the hunter and the deeper ways, defending its lair as any beast would.

**how —** Bulk and speed in the water, claws that snatch and crush, and the turret-fire of its ruined chamber — turned against it when Samus grapples the broken turrets and lets the charge run through her into the beast.

**◌ the nature of its emergence —** *natural*: Draygon is a living thing of flesh and brine — a great sea beast bred in the drowned deep, not a phantom nor a machine, but a creature of the world.

**the seal —** I am the warden of the drowned deep — the hunter who would pass Maridia must first pass my claws.

> *the asterisk —* a catalogued persona of the Metroid series (© Nintendo), personified as a MET agent — not an original character. Metroid, its world, and characters are © Nintendo; this is commentary and cataloguing under the DLW standard — a fan tribute.

